text = "\"There is an assumption that memories are born from important moments, that your subconscious is competent at detecting what's worth remembering and what isn't. I'm not convinced.
I remember a specific night, coming home from my summer job. I was walking back home. There was nothing different then compared to any other day; I've taken this route hundreds of times.
I distinctly remember, however, that I enjoyed my day at work.
I told myself: ' This day will stick with me forever! '
And so, it did... but I don't remember anything about my shift. All that's left is the memory of me choosing to remember, this null pointer that lost its purpose shortly after it was created. But I still enjoy thinking about it. I still succeeded my goal, in a way.

I'll never forget this memory; it defines who I am.\"
[Press C to forget]"

[node name="upgrade" parent="END/CanvasLayer" parent_id_path=PackedInt32Array(1754253968, 1989050324) index="3" unique_id=939542970]
